          <fields>
            <field>
              <name>LP_I2C_COMMAND0</name>
              <description>This is the content of command 0. It consists of three parts: op_code is the command, 1: WRITE, 2: STOP, 3: READ, 4: END, 6: RSTART. Byte_num represents the number of bytes that need to be sent or received.ack_check_en, ack_exp and ack are used to control the ACK bit. See I2C cmd structure for moreInformation.</description>
